# ==============================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==============================================

# 1. Go to https://marketplace.zoom.us/
# 2. Sign in with your Zoom account
# 3. Click "Develop" â†’ "Build App"
# 4. Choose app type based on your needs:
#    - "Server-to-Server OAuth" (recommended for backend-to-backend)
#    - "OAuth" (for user authorization)
# 5. Fill in app information and get credentials
# 6. Add redirect URI: http://localhost:8000/api/zoom/oauth/callback (for local dev)
# 7. For production, add: https://yourdomain.com/api/zoom/oauth/callback
# 8. Enable required scopes (see ZOOM_INTEGRATION.md for full list)
# 9. For Web SDK, create a separate "Meeting SDK" app
# 10. Copy all credentials to your .env files

# ==============================================
# REQUIRED OAUTH SCOPES
# ==============================================

# meeting:write - Create meetings
# meeting:read - Read meeting details
# meeting:update - Update meetings
# meeting:delete - Delete meetings
# user:read - Read user profile
# recording:read - Access recordings

# ==============================================
# PRODUCTION NOTES
# ==============================================

# In production:
# 1. Use HTTPS for redirect URIs
# 2. Store secrets securely (environment variables, not in code)
# 3. Enable token encryption in database
# 4. Set up webhook endpoints for meeting events
# 5. Configure rate limiting
# 6. Enable audit logging

